  },
  {
    question: "What EV enquiries come through Messenger?",
    answer: "New EV owners wanting a charger before their vehicle arrives. Existing EV owners frustrated with three-pin charging speeds wanting an upgrade. Homeowners with solar panels wanting a Zappi for excess solar charging. Office managers needing workplace chargers for their team. Property developers requesting per-plot charger pre-wiring. Each sender has pre-assessed your OZEV-approved installation quality from your Facebook gallery."
  },
  {
    question: "How fast does the AI reply to EV messages?",
    answer: "Replies arrive within seconds of every incoming Messenger enquiry. Facebook's activity badge confirms your EV firm actively monitors. A new Audi Q8 e-tron owner collecting Saturday morning — currently imagining the three-pin socket adding 15 miles overnight then a 250-mile Monday commute — demands an immediate, authoritative response from an OZEV-approved installer, not a page whose last charger photo was posted six weeks ago."
  },
  {
    question: "What does Messenger cost for EV installers?",
    answer: `Facebook Messenger is an add-on at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month. A domestic charger installation generates £800 to £1,500. One homeowner's Easee installation — initiated by a Messenger enquiry after she saw your neighbour's charger glowing on the garage wall — covers the annual channel cost from a single installation.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I continue Messenger conversations personally?",
    answer: "Respond once in any Messenger thread and the AI steps aside permanently. Most EV installers let the AI collect the initial specification — vehicle model, charger preference, mounting position, cable run, supply type, and grant interest — then take over to discuss the earthing arrangement, consumer unit upgrade, and the installation date."
  },
  {
